    {
      "note_no": "270",
      "note": "Him in whose hands is the marriage tie : According to Hanaf i doctrine this is the husband himself, who can ordinarily by his act dissolve the marriage. It therefore behoves him to be all the more liberal to the woman and pay her the full dower even if the marriage was not consummated."
